You are The Empress

Beauty, happiness, pleasure, success, luxury, dissipation.

The Empress is associated with Venus, the feminine planet, so it represents, beauty, charm, pleasure, luxury, and delight. You may be good at home decorating, art or anything to do with making things beautiful.

The Empress is a creator, be it creation of life, of romance, of art or business. While the Magician is the primal spark, the idea made real, and the High Priestess is the one who gives the idea a form, the Empress is the womb where it gestates and grows till it is ready to be born. This is why her symbol is Venus, goddess of beautiful things as well as love. Even so, the Empress is more Demeter, goddess of abundance, then sensual Venus. She is the giver of Earthly gifts, yet at the same time, she can, in anger withhold, as Demeter did when her daughter, Persephone, was kidnapped. In fury and grief, she kept the Earth barren till her child was returned to her.

Walk with me, the path of life,
to explore every bend of the road
Enjoy with me the beauty of life,
along its wonderful way

Find comfort with me, in each other's arms,
when grief crosses our path
Find strength with me, in each other's strength,
when despair lies in wait

Laugh with me, a single true laugh,
to enlighten another's distress
Cry with me, a single true tear,
to understand true happiness

Cherish with me, the wonders of life,
as they need to be preserved
Rejoice with me, in the mysteries,
of what is yet to be

Find peace with me, in each other's souls,
when the world has gone insane
Find love with me, in each other's hearts,
until this life has been fulfilled

And when the path comes to an end
I hope we can say from within
We've known the beauty of true love,
our love came from within

On Saturday. Got my hair done! A new color. Very nice. Everyone loves it. Hung out with my friend Gis and her daughter, very much fun.

Sunday, Went to my best friends place last night, we drank a bottle of wine together, watched movies and relaxed. Which was awesome since it's only now 5 more days till the wedding. Helped her with the wedding favours. She's getting the jitters and I'm nervous for her as well. I mean I've known her for 10 years. My goodness how time flies, and now she's getting married. Wow.. can't wait for my own(but I can) Then at Midnight she drove me home (well her fiancee did lol) 

(Mon) And then today I slept in, and my mother drove out to my friends mothers house. There we had a surprise wedding shower for her. Which was lots of fun. Chocolate fountain! Woo! 
(And yes I had some, so don't comment on it.)
Then after, my mom and I went to see the movie Disturbia. Which was awesome. 

Now at home relaxing..

Remind me again why I bother to try and be nice to people and they treat you like crap in return, yet I deal with it. I mean I try and be nice, and I get ignored. Gotta enjoy that. yup. well I will change. 
Bah.. Forget me being nice to everyone anymore. You all can fend for yourselves. 
Those who are still nice, will continue to see the old me. The others.. Can kiss my a$$.

Well I'm on my fourth day of no coffee. It's weird, but now I can see why it's so addicting to have caffeine. I've had  a headache everyday since I stopped. But today. No more headaches. Also I'm waking up at 0530 on the dot. So it is better for my system. I'm having Mint Tea. Plus No more pop for me. Cutting back on all sugary goodness. The only day I'm gonna have something sweet is this Friday And a tiny bite on Saturday. Then I'm back on the diet. I'm losing weight still. Slow and steady. But starting on Monday I'm beginning a new 28 day program. Should work out all right. 

 Well I start a new class at the college tonight. Intro to Social and Cultural Anthropology. Luckily I have two good friends that are taking the same course!
So I'm excited!

The party for my friend is coming along. Rather quickly and I still feel not ready but what can I do. Just have to make it fun for her. 

Other than that. I get to see my tiger this Friday Night <3 yay. 

On Sunday I think I might go to the pool and fitness centre. So if anyone wants to join me they can..

That's all for now.. ^_^

Your Personality Is
Idealist (NF)
You are a passionate, caring, and unique person. You are good at expressing yourself and sharing your ideals. You are the most compassionate of all types and connect with others easily. Your heart tends to rule you. You can't make decisions without considering feelings. You seek out other empathetic people to befriend. Truth and authenticity matters in your friendships. In love, you give everything you have to relationships. You fall in love easily. At work, you crave personal expression and meaning in your career. With others, you communicate well. You can spend all night talking with someone. As far as your looks go, you've likely taken the time to develop your own personal style. On weekends, you like to be with others. Charity work is also a favorite pastime of yours.
The Three Question Personality Test

You Are a Peacemaker Soul
You strive to please others and compromise anyway you can. War or conflict bothers you, and you would do anything to keep the peace. You are a good mediator and a true negotiator. Sometimes you do too much, trying so hard to make people happy. While you keep the peace, you tend to be secretly judgmental. You lose respect for people who don't like to both give and take. On the flip side, you've got a graet sense of humor and wit. You're always dimplomatic and able to give good advice. Souls you are most compatible with: Warrior Soul, Hunter Soul and Visionary Soul
What Kind of Soul Are You?

Anyways I'm off to daydreaming again. And talking to Kitteh about seal slippers for her gaia thing. Hehe

Ok. I absolutely hate my job. I get in trouble for the most stupid reasons. Aww They weren't paid cause this particular thing wasn't on the call list. Omg. Boo fucking whoo. Omg if we weren't supposed to do that, then you should have informed everyone not to send anyone. Gawd. Freaking crybabies. I don't know how much longer I can handle this job without have a nervous breakdown. It's like stepping on eggshells. One mistep and you get whipped over and over again because you did something not right. Were we informed on how to follow the instructions they know. No! We're somehow supposed to be mind readers. And do everything perfectly without mistake. Oh Wait. We're only freaking human. We all make mistakes. In my case Ok this didn't go right but don't go about accusing me of making the company lose money becuase the person who requested something is refusing to pay. Shit.. I mean give me a break. Go freaking cry and whine about it to someone else. Bah I hate my job. I hate it with a passion. But what else can I do. I need to pay off my bills. So I can then get a different job and and do something else. But we all know other jobs don't pay as much. bah.. I need a new Job and new managers. I believe I'm done ranting for now..

My God Father tells me that she had been at the Clinic due to some pain in her leg. Then the clinic had sent her to Royal Columbian. He says not to Panic... Well Pfft to that. Of course I'll panic. This is my mom. But anyways. I headed down to the hospital, met up with my mom and Auntie Heather. Perfect timing. Though my mom is ok. But she will have to get an ultrasound on her leg for precautions incase there might be more to the blood clot found in her leg. Though she is now on medication.. 
I've brought her home. But still the worry is there until we can get her in for that ultrasound. 

I'll be honest.. she's scared. As, am I. I don't really want to anything bad to happen. But I will believe that all will be ok.
